the same old apartment, same old job...

13
00:00:46,385 --> 00:00:49,368
- sometimes it just
- Er, Russell, we're just about at the end of our hour.

14
00:00:49,936 --> 00:00:53,881
Let me see if I can cut to the chase by using  myself as an example.

15
00:00:54,710 --> 00:00:57,380
Six months ago, I was living in Boston.

16
00:00:58,051 --> 00:01:01,387
My wife had left me, which was very painful.

17
00:01:01,747 --> 00:01:04,326
Then she came back to me, which was excruciating.

18
00:01:10,078 --> 00:01:14,915
On top of that, my practice had grown stagnant, and my social life consisted of...

19
00:01:16,063 --> 00:01:18,502
hanging around a bar night after night.

20
00:01:20,013 --> 00:01:23,218
You see, I was clinging to a life that wasn't working anymore

21
00:01:23,219 --> 00:01:25,948
and I knew I had to do something, anything.

22
00:01:25,949 --> 00:01:27,774
So, I ended the marriage once and for all,

23
00:01:27,775 --> 00:01:31,145
packed up my things, and moved back here to my hometown of Seattle

24
00:01:31,146 --> 00:01:32,414
Go Seahawks!

25
00:01:33,518 --> 00:01:35,185
I took action, Russell.

26
00:01:35,444 --> 00:01:36,572
And you can, too.

27
00:01:36,573 --> 00:01:39,081
Move, change, do something,

28
00:01:39,082 --> 00:01:41,266
if it's a mistake, do something else.

29
00:01:41,955 --> 00:01:43,230
Will you do that, Russell?

30
00:01:45,015 --> 00:01:46,090
Will you?

31
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:48,080
Russell...?

32
00:01:48,941 --> 00:01:49,948
I think we lost him.

33
00:01:50,297 --> 00:01:52,764
No, we cut to the news thirty seconds ago.

34
00:01:56,308 --> 00:01:57,694
Oh, for crying out loud!

35
00:01:58,611 --> 00:02:00,463
I finally bare my soul to all of Seattle,

36
00:02:00,464 --> 00:02:03,132
and they're listening to Chopper Dave's "Rush-Hour Round-Up!"

37
00:02:05,843 --> 00:02:07,418
Well, the rest of the show was pretty good.

38
00:02:09,215 --> 00:02:10,929
It was a, a good show, wasn't it?

39
